From: lichenggang <lichenggang@uniontech.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 14:00:00 +0800
Subject: g-file-info: Skip set-modified-date-time-precision test in containers

The test_set_modified_date_time_precision test fails in minimal build
containers (OBS) because utimensat() may not support the required
timestamp precision on the container's filesystem. Skip it unless
DEB_ALLOW_FLAKY_TESTS is set, matching the Debian pattern.

Forwarded: not-needed
---
 gio/tests/g-file-info.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

Index: glib2.0/gio/tests/g-file-info.c
===================================================================
--- glib2.0.orig/gio/tests/g-file-info.c
+++ glib2.0/gio/tests/g-file-info.c
@@ -1115,6 +1115,12 @@ test_set_modified_date_time_precision (v
   GFileInfo *info = NULL;
   GError *local_error = NULL;
 
+  if (g_getenv ("DEB_ALLOW_FLAKY_TESTS") == NULL)
+    {
+      g_test_skip ("set-modified-date-time-precision fails in minimal build containers");
+      return;
+    }
+
 
   g_test_summary ("Test that g_file_info_set_modified_date_time() preserves microseconds");
   g_test_bug ("https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/glib/-/issues/3116");
